## üöÄ Installation Method
Easy installation with `pip install`.

```sh
pip install monitor-app
```

---

## üîß Usage

### **1Ô∏è‚É£ Create a New Project**
```sh
monitor-app startproject <project_name>
```
üìå **Example: Create template with the name my_project**
```sh
monitor-app startproject my_project
```
‚û° Creates a Monitor-app application template in the `my_project` folder.


### **2Ô∏è‚É£ Register CSV to Database**
```sh
cd my_project
python <project_name>/app.py import-csv
```
‚û° Converts CSV files in the `csv/` folder to SQLite database.

### **3Ô∏è‚É£ Start Web Application**
```sh
python <project_name>/app.py runserver
```
‚û° Access `http://127.0.0.1:9990`!

### **üìå `runserver` Options**
| Option | Description |
|------------|--------------------------------|
| `--csv`   | Register CSV before starting  |
| `--debug` | Start in debug mode    |
| `--port <PORT>` | Specify port (default: 9990) |

üìå **Example: Start after registering CSV**
```sh
python <project_name>/app.py runserver --csv
```

üìå **Example: Start in debug mode on port `8000`**
```sh
python <project_name>/app.py runserver --debug --port 8000
```

